{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Reevaluating concepts of domestication\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A framework in which crops were domesticated from a single population or even a single species is, in several instances, an oversimplification. A demography incorporating introgression from additional sources appears to be more correct for many crops. With this in mind, certain aspects of crop evolution must be reevaluated:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab The initial domestication bottleneck is most likely underestimated when introgression is not considered. Chromosomal regions experiencing introgression will potentially have increased effective population size relative to non-introgressed regions. Inferences regarding the strength of domestication bottlenecks should be revisited with this in mind.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab The time since domestication based on levels of sequence divergence may be inflated when introgressed haplotypes from divergent taxa are included in estimates.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab The influx of diversity through introgression may belie selection occurring on these genomic regions during domestication or local adaptation since one of the hallmarks of selection is reduced diversity.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Future studies in crop-wild introgression\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Additional study of introgression in agroecosystems could lead to advances in both basic and applied genetics:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Basic questions:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 a.\tx360\tab To what extent does the level of introgression across taxa depend on divergence time between donor and recipient taxa?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 b.\tx360\tab At what geographic scale does adaptive introgression occur? Is introgression frequently restricted to very local populations or is it often seen over broad geographic ranges?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 c.\tx360\tab To what extent have domesticates served as bridges for gene flow between previously allopatric taxa?\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Applications:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 a.\tx360\tab Loci underlying the domesticated phenotype that are potentially beneficial targets for crop improvement can be more clearly identified by removing the confounding population genetic signal of introgression.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 b.\tx360\tab Adaptive introgression that is clearly tied to a specific environment may include beneficial alleles that can be utilized in crop breeding.\sa180\sa180\par}
